C TC04
(* JMM causality test case 4 (Pugh 2004). Same as TC03 but BOTH arms of P0's guard  *)
(* write x=1, so the store happens unconditionally with a fixed value: the control   *)
(* dependency is REDUNDANT (fake). JMM DECISION: ALLOWED (a compiler may remove the   *)
(* redundant branch). LIMITATION: the wev C parser has no brace/else handling, so     *)
(* both-arms-write flattens to the SAME event structure as genuine TC03 and records   *)
(* the ctrl edge isSemantic=true unconditionally -- it cannot see both arms write 1.  *)
(* Intended source: P0: r0=READ(y); if(r0==1) x=1 else x=1.                           *)
{ }
P0(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*y); if (r0 == 1) ; WRITE_ONCE(*x, 1); }
P1(int *x, int *y) { r0 = READ_ONCE(*x); WRITE_ONCE(*y, r0 + 1); }
exists (0:r0=1 /\ 1:r0=1)
